{"insight":"Know when the road is done","publicTitle":"When the Road Is Done","plainSummary":"A helpful path must also teach us when to keep it, release it, or let it become daily life.","atAGlance":"Strong insight can still become another way to prove our worth. A trustworthy path teaches what it changes and how to carry it afterward. Some paths stay as steady help. Some should be set down, and some should become quiet conduct.","keyPoints":["Real growth includes knowing how to live after the breakthrough.","Insight can feed self-worth hunger when it becomes a badge.","Look for kinder conduct after the exercise, not just stronger feelings."],"match":["the road must know its end"],"tags":["practice","insight","restraint"]}
